section.section:
The following persons are exempt from the requirements of this section:
A person who is operating a vessel in connection with commercial purposes;
A person who is a resident of another state and who is visiting the State for 60 days or less in a vessel that is numbered in another state if:
The person is 16 years old or older; or
The person has been issued a boating safety certificate in accordance with the provisions of subsection (c)(6) of this section;
A person who is visiting the State for 90 days or less in a vessel from a country other than the United States;
A person operating a vessel on a body of water located on private property; and
Any other person exempted by regulation of the Department.

The Department shall:
Adopt regulations that establish criteria for a course of instruction in boating safety education;
Administer a verbal test when appropriate;
Coordinate a statewide program of boating safety instruction and certification and ensure that a course of boating safety education is available within each county; and
Ensure that a course of boating safety education is available at the earliest practicable age for children in boating communities.

The following persons may offer the course of instruction in boating safety education if approved by the Department:
The Department;
The U.S. Coast Guard Auxiliary;
The U.S. Power Squadron;
A political subdivision;
A municipal corporation;
An agency;
A public or nonpublic school;
A group;
A firm;
An association; or
Any other person.
